  "body": "How can I run a node as a full node and how can I sync my node via fast sync?\r\n- Because by default running is an archive node\r\n- And I could not see anything how to specify synchronization because I want fast sync not full sync.\r\nI created this command after some investigation in order to handle full node, in there I tried to reach state data after block number 5000000. Is this correct for what I want?\r\n./build/bin/erigon --datadir rinkeby --chain rinkeby --prune=hrtc --prune.h.before=5000000 --prune.r.before=5000000 --prune.t.before=5000000 --prune.c.before=5000000\r\nBut how can I specify fast sync to this command?",
